omg dan! i've been watching you since "my name is [dan]", and i...
body:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lrwMja_VoM0&feature=youtu.be

omg dan! i’ve been watching you since “my name is [dan]”, and i have to say you’ve evolved into an amazing and beautiful individual! this takes so much courage, and we as the phandom are extremely proud of you!! it was so heartwarming when you mentioned phil, even if it was for a brief moment. this was such a powerful message- i didn’t know how much i needed to hear this. thank you so much for sharing , and happy pride month 🏳️‍🌈. as soon as i saw the title, i teared up. dan, you never fail to make me, and the rest of phandom laugh, cry or full of joy. you’re an icon for all those waiting to come out to their friends and family. even when this video wasn’t out, you were the one who gave me the courage to come out, and i’m pretty sure, countless others…. love you, welcome to the gay internet mafia lol and good luck on your journey as a wonderful, new version of yourself!! 🥰🥰

summary: Daniel Howell
body:
Daniel Howell

So I watched Dan’s coming out video a little while ago, and honestly I am so proud of him for it. I’m not gay, so I don’t know what that feels like and I never will, but I can sympathize with it to a certain degree. I know it’s scary. Him coming out and finally saying the words “I’m gay” aren’t what really hit me though.

It was what he said about suicide, about him attempting and then being so thankful that he failed. Because life does get better. It does. There comes a time where the clouds part and you’ll be glad you kept hanging on, pushing and waiting for those days to come. It’s something I have believed in my heart for a long time and seeing someone like Dan, who we all know has a history of struggling with this kind of thing- it just makes me so happy. Somehow it struck me as a kind of peaceful confidence coming from him, something I can relate back to him for myself.

I love Dan. But I’ve never had anything real I could relate with. Now that I do, that I know we’re both stronger people for fighting even though we both have been in such dark places, it makes me happy in a way.

This post makes absolutely no sense but, yeah. I haven’t seen many people talk about his growth from attempting suicide and to me that is a huge accomplishment that needs to be praised.

I don’t watch d&p as much as when I was younger, but still.

I love you Daniel Howell and I am so proud of you and of all the strength you’ve learned to wield over the years. @danielhowell 🖤💘

trail.content_raw:
Daniel Howell

So I watched Dan’s coming out video a little while ago, and honestly I am so proud of him for it. I’m not gay, so I don’t know what that feels like and I never will, but I can sympathize with it to a certain degree. I know it’s scary. Him coming out and finally saying the words “I’m gay” aren’t what really hit me though.

It was what he said about suicide, about him attempting and then being so thankful that he failed. Because life does get better. It does. There comes a time where the clouds part and you’ll be glad you kept hanging on, pushing and waiting for those days to come. It’s something I have believed in my heart for a long time and seeing someone like Dan, who we all know has a history of struggling with this kind of thing- it just makes me so happy. Somehow it struck me as a kind of peaceful confidence coming from him, something I can relate back to him for myself.

I love Dan. But I’ve never had anything real I could relate with. Now that I do, that I know we’re both stronger people for fighting even though we both have been in such dark places, it makes me happy in a way.

summary: JSEgo Headcanon (2): Alternatives
title: JSEgo Headcanon (2): Alternatives
body:
Antisepticeye and Jameson Jackson go to a lot of concerts together–specifically various kinds of rock concerts (alternative, metal, etc.).

The reason being: it doesn’t matter how loud it gets, if they have earplugs in, or if there’s space between them; as long as they can keep an eye on each other, they can always hear each other perfectly via Sign Language.

summary: You’re not allowed to share Dan Howell’s coming out vid if you’re just gonna share the “Basically I’m gay!!” clip. It totally...
body: You’re not allowed to share Dan Howell’s coming out vid if you’re just gonna share the “Basically I’m gay!!” clip. It totally misses the point on a video about internalized homophobia and the struggles that come with it AND it’s completely disregarding the part where he talks about how strangers grossly speculating about peoples sexuality and orientation can be dangerous and damaging to them. As an outsider whose never watched a single Dan and Phil clip before this one I really love that he called out how horrifying and invasive fans digging into his private life was as someone in the closet to his family. If you are in any way someone who obsesses over straight/maybe closeted celebrities please let this be a lesson on how much it actually hurts real people, especially the people you admire so much.
